    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Glassware with facets, grooves, and depressions produced by cutting with a rotating wheel of metal or stone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021271/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Glass (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese en general para describir objetos de vidrio con facetas, ranuras y depresiones, producidas por corte con una rueda giratoria de metal o piedra.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doorgaans te gebruiken voor glaswerk met facetten, groeven en holtes die worden verkregen door te snijden met een ronddraaiend wiel van metaal of steen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
